###Login
# az login 

###create service account
# az ad sp create-for-rbac --role="Contributor" --scopes="/subscriptions{subscriptionID}"
## AppId = ClientID
## Password = ClientSecret

###generate ssh key
# ssh-keygen -m PEM -t rsa -b 4096

###Connect to Cluster
# az aks get-credentials --name k8stest_dev --resource-group kubernetes_dev

###See the service of the cluster connected
# kubectl get service

###get credentials
# az aks get-credentials --name k8stest_dev --resource-group kubernetes_dev --admin

###display details of config
# cat ~/.kube/config

### Add all terraform and aws tools to the DevOps Project via Visual Studio Marketplace

### Create all necessary Service Connections for each AWS and Terraform on DevOps


### Kubernetes service connetion to the kubernetes(url & secret) on DevOps
# kubectl cluster-info
###get secret name
# kubectl get serviceaccounts default -o yaml
###get secret token
# kubelct get secret default-token hdkfg -o yaml

###get cofiguration aws with the cluster
# aws eks --region eu-west-2 update-kubeconfig --name badalo-cluster